", \"from\": 388, \"to\": 396}, {\"ngram\": \"the unforgettableLondon2012 Games\", \"from\": 417, \"to\": 450}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Metro.co.uk's live blog for latest updates on the 2024 Olympic Games Of those 64 medals in Tokyo, 22 were the top prize, with Great Britain andNorthern Irelandexperiencing a steady decline in the number of gold medals since an all-time best haul of 29 in London.\", \"from\": 453, \"to\": 723, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 552, \"end\": 557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9998331782936667, \"rank\": 0.00016684931535419632, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 587, \"end\": 600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.99716477697362, \"rank\": 0.002843279755065805, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 716, \"end\": 722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999752211434053, \"rank\": 2.442266553154248e-05, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Follow Metro.co.uk's live blog\", \"from\": 453, \"to\": 483}, {\"ngram\": \"latest updates\", \"from\": 488, \"to\": 502}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympic Games\", \"from\": 506, \"to\": 528}, {\"ngram\": \"those 64 medals\", \"from\": 532, \"to\": 547}, {\"ngram\": \"the top prize\", \"from\": 566, \"to\": 579}, {\"ngram\": \"a steady decline\", \"from\": 632, \"to\": 648}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 652, \"to\": 662}, {\"ngram\": \"gold medals\", \"from\": 666, \"to\": 677}, {\"ngram\": \"an all-time best haul\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 705}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, after a tenth-placed finish at Athens 2004, Team GB have secured a place in the top four each of the last four Olympics, a streak that will continue if their targets are met.\", \"from\": 725, \"to\": 908, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 778, \"end\": 785, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9993164310472883, \"rank\": 0.0006769837195087537, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a tenth-placed finish\", \"from\": 740, \"to\": 761}, {\"ngram\": \"Athens\", \"from\": 765, \"to\": 771}, {\"ngram\": \"a place\", \"from\": 799, \"to\": 806}, {\"ngram\": \"the last four Olympics\", \"from\": 831, \"to\": 853}, {\"ngram\": \"a streak\", \"from\": 855, \"to\": 863}, {\"ngram\": \"their targets\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 899}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking ahead of the Games, UK Sport's Director of Performance, Kate Baker, revealed that Team GB had been set an official target of between 50 and 70 medals.\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 1069, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 939, \"end\": 947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UK Sport\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\"}, {\"begin\": 975, \"end\": 985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Baker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Baker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Baker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Baker\"}, {\"begin\": 1001, \"end\": 1008, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9993164310472883, \"rank\": 0.0006769837195087537, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 928, \"to\": 937}, {\"ngram\": \"Performance\", \"from\": 962, \"to\": 973}, {\"ngram\": \"an official target\", \"from\": 1022, \"to\": 1040}, {\"ngram\": \"between 50 and 70 medals\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1068}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'We are likely to be the only nation, other than the USA or China, who will be bold enough to say that we can go to these Games and come home with a minimum of 50 medals,' Baker said.\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1254, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1124, \"end\": 1127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9296743308430593, \"rank\": 0.07563952822427591, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1131, \"end\": 1136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.736130503995458, \"rank\": 0.3496009213277626, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1243, \"end\": 1248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Baker\", \"score\": 0.889947919263775, \"rank\": 0.11330061922762724, \"text\": \"Baker\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Baker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Baker\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the only nation\", \"from\": 1092, \"to\": 1107}, {\"ngram\": \"these Games\", \"from\": 1187, \"to\": 1198}, {\"ngram\": \"a minimum\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1227}, {\"ngram\": \"50 medals\", \"from\": 1231, \"to\": 1240}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'That is an extraordinary achievement.\", \"from\": 1256, \"to\": 1294, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an extraordinary achievement\", \"from\": 1265, \"to\": 1293}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Whilst we have achieved more than that historically, and I feel somewhat confident that we can do so again - 50 is no mean feat and it is not a done deal.\", \"from\": 1295, \"to\": 1449, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no mean feat\", \"from\": 1410, \"to\": 1422}, {\"ngram\": \"a done deal\", \"from\": 1437, \"to\": 1448}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'We want to continue our streak of top five Olympic medal table finishes.\", \"from\": 1451, \"to\": 1524, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our streak\", \"from\": 1472, \"to\": 1482}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are feeling confident that we are on an upward trajectory as we head towards the Games.\", \"from\": 1525, \"to\": 1615, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an upward trajectory\", \"from\": 1565, \"to\": 1585}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1605, \"to\": 1614}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'We feel very confident that we will get between 50 and 70 medals and that on a good day that 70 is really within our grasp.'\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1742, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"between 50 and 70 medals\", \"from\": 1658, \"to\": 1682}, {\"ngram\": \"a good day\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1705}, {\"ngram\": \"our grasp\", \"from\": 1731, \"to\": 1740}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Looking ahead to the Games,OLBG's SuperComputer predicted that Team GB would win 26 gold, 16 silver and 20 bronze medals, with the USA topping the overall medals table.\", \"from\": 1744, \"to\": 1912, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1771, \"end\": 1775, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/OLBG\", \"score\": 0.9999712913264474, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"OLBG\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/OLBG\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/